I89. Definitions

I11As used in this title_

I12(1) ``Postal Service'' means the United States Postal Service established by section 201 of this title;

I12(2) ``Board of Governors'', and ``Board'', unless the context otherwise requires, mean the Board of Governors established under section 202 of this title;

I12(3) ``Governors'' means the 9 members of the Board of Governors appointed by the President, by and with the advice and consent of the Senate, under section 202(a) of this title;

I12(4) ``Inspector General'' means the Inspector General appointed under section 202(e) of this title;

I12(5) ``postal service'' refers to the delivery of letters, printed matter, or mailable packages, including acceptance, collection, sorting, transportation, or other functions ancillary thereto;

I12(6) ``product'' means a postal service with a distinct cost or market characteristic for which a rate or rates are, or may reasonably be, applied;

I12(7) ``rates'', as used with respect to products, includes fees for postal services;

I12(8) ``market-dominant product'' or ``product in the market-dominant category of mail'' means a product subject to subchapter I of chapter 36;

I12(9) ``competitive product'' or ``product in the competitive category of mail'' means a product subject to subchapter II of chapter 36; and

I12(10) ``year'', as used in chapter 36 (other than subchapters I and VI thereof), means a fiscal year.

