I89. Nonmailable skill contests or sweepstakes matter; notification to prohibit mailings

I11(a) T4DefinitionsK._In this section_

I12(1) the term ``promoter'' means any person who_

I13(A) originates and mails any skill contest or sweepstakes, except for any matter described in section 3001(k)(4); or

I13(B) originates and causes to be mailed any skill contest or sweepstakes, except for any matter described in section 3001(k)(4);

Q04

I12(2) the term ``removal request'' means a request stating that an individual elects to have the name and address of such individual excluded from any list used by a promoter for mailing skill contests or sweepstakes;

I12(3) the terms ``skill contest'', ``sweepstakes'', and ``clearly and conspicuously displayed'' have the same meanings as given them in section 3001(k); and

I12(4) the term ``duly authorized person'', as used in connection with an individual, means a conservator or guardian of, or person granted power of attorney by, such individual.

Q04

I11(b) T4Nonmailable Matter._

I12(1) T4In generalK._Matter otherwise legally acceptable in the mails described in paragraph (2)_

I13(A) is nonmailable matter;

I13(B) shall not be carried or delivered by mail; and

I13(C) shall be disposed of as the Postal Service directs.

Q04

I12(2) T4Nonmailable matter describedK._Matter described in this paragraph is any matter that_

I13(A) is a skill contest or sweepstakes, except for any matter described in section 3001(k)(4); and

I13(B)(i) is addressed to an individual who made an election to be excluded from lists under subsection (d); or

I13(ii) does not comply with subsection (c)(1).

Q04

I11(c) T4Requirements of Promoters._

I12(1) T4Notice to individualsK._Any promoter who mails a skill contest or sweepstakes shall provide with each mailing a statement that_

I13(A) is clearly and conspicuously displayed;

I13(B) includes the address or toll-free telephone number of the notification system established under paragraph (2); and

I13(C) states that the notification system may be used to prohibit the mailing of all skill contests or sweepstakes by that promoter to such individual.

Q04

I12(2) T4Notification systemK._Any promoter that mails or causes to be mailed a skill contest or sweepstakes shall establish and maintain a notification system that provides for any individual (or other duly authorized person) to notify the system of the individual's election to have the name and address of the individual excluded from all lists of names and addresses used by that promoter to mail any skill contest or sweepstakes.

Q04

I11(d) T4Election To Be Excluded From Lists._

I12(1) T4In generalK._An individual (or other duly authorized person) may elect to exclude the name and address of that individual from all lists of names and addresses used by a promoter of skill contests or sweepstakes by submitting a removal request to the notification system established under subsection (c).

I12(2) T4Response after submitting removal request to the notification systemK._Not later than 60 calendar days after a promoter receives a removal request pursuant to an election under paragraph (1), the promoter shall exclude the individual's name and address from all lists of names and addresses used by that promoter to select recipients for any skill contest or sweepstakes.

I12(3) T4Effectiveness of electionK._An election under paragraph (1) shall remain in effect, unless an individual (or other duly authorized person) notifies the promoter in writing that such individual_

I13(A) has changed the election; and

I13(B) elects to receive skill contest or sweepstakes mailings from that promoter.

Q04

I11(e) T4Private Right of Action._

I12(1) T4In generalK._An individual who receives one or more mailings in violation of subsection (d) may, if otherwise permitted by the laws or rules of court of a State, bring in an appropriate court of that State_

I13(A) an action to enjoin such violation;

I13(B) an action to recover for actual monetary loss from such a violation, or to receive $500 in damages for each such violation, whichever is greater; or

I13(C) both such actions.

Q04

I17It shall be an affirmative defense in any action brought under this subsection that the defendant has established and implemented, with due care, reasonable practices and procedures to effectively prevent mailings in violation of subsection (d). If the court finds that the defendant willfully or knowingly violated subsection (d), the court may, in its discretion, increase the amount of the award to an amount equal to not more than 3 times the amount available under subparagraph (B).

I12(2) T4Action allowable based on other sufficient noticeK._A mailing sent in violation of section 3001(T3lK) shall be actionable under this subsection, but only if such an action would not also be available under paragraph (1) (as a violation of subsection (d)) based on the same mailing.

Q04

I11(f) T4Promoter NonliabilityK._A promoter shall not be subject to civil liability for the exclusion of an individual's name or address from any list maintained by that promoter for mailing skill contests or sweepstakes, if_

I12(1) a removal request is received by the promoter's notification system; and

I12(2) the promoter has a good faith belief that the request is from_

