I11(h) T4Civil Penalties._

I12(1) T4In generalK._Any promoter_

I13(A) who recklessly mails nonmailable matter in violation of subsection (b) shall be liable to the United States in an amount of $10,000 per violation for each mailing to an individual of nonmailable matter; or

I13(B) who fails to comply with the requirements of subsection (c)(2) shall be liable to the United States.

Q04

I12(2) T4EnforcementK._The Postal Service shall, in accordance with the same procedures as set forth in section 3012(b), provide for the assessment of civil penalties under this section.

